### CSS Tables

Style HTML tables with borders, spacing, and striping.

---

### Table Properties

| Property | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `border-collapse` | Single or separate borders |
| `border-spacing` | Distance between cell borders |
| `caption-side` | Caption position (top/bottom) |
| `empty-cells` | Show/hide empty cell borders |
| `table-layout` | Algorithm for table width |

---

### Border Collapse

```css
table {
  border-collapse: collapse;  /* Single borders (recommended) */
  border-collapse: separate; /* Default - double borders */
}
```

---

### Basic Table Styling

```css
table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
}

th, td {
  padding: 12px 16px;
  text-align: left;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
}

th {
  background: #f5f5f5;
  font-weight: bold;
}
```

---

### Striped Rows

```css
tr:nth-child(even) {
  background: #f9f9f9;
}

tr:hover {
  background: #f0f0f0;
}
```

---

### Table Layout

```css
table {
  table-layout: auto;   /* Default - size based on content */
  table-layout: fixed;  /* Equal columns, faster rendering */
}
```

`table-layout: fixed` gives more predictable widths, especially for large tables.

---

### Responsive Tables

```css
.table-container {
  overflow-x: auto;  /* Horizontal scroll on small screens */
}
```

Wrap table in `<div class="table-container">`.

---

### Complete Example

```css
table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  font-size: 15px;
}

th {
  background: #2c3e50;
  color: white;
  padding: 12px 15px;
  text-align: left;
}

td {
  padding: 10px 15px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
}

tr:nth-child(even) {
  background: #f8f8f8;
}

tr:hover {
  background: #e8f4ff;
}
```

> **Best Practice:** Always use `border-collapse: collapse`. Use `overflow-x: auto` for responsive tables.
